D. THE CONTRACTOR LETTER  (Section 5 lab maintenance file)
-----------------------------------------------------------------
NOTE TO GM: Antoine has kept and studied the SLEEPING Ulag his whole life -- his family held
the Breaker in stasis for generations before the Cult woke him for the war. The Ice-Shaper
is the contractor who built the casket and who moves minds between bodies. This letter names
the METHOD and the contractor, and nothing else. No victim is named or implied. Its power is
dramatic irony the AUDIENCE may feel and the characters cannot place. Read it flat.
THE LETTER (the Ice-Shaper to Antoine; in the maintenance file):
  "You have kept the Breaker's frame the way your father kept it and his father before him,
   and called the keeping devotion. The frame was always the small problem. Holding a mind in
   failing flesh is a nursemaid's work, and your family has done nursemaid's work with great
   patience for a very long time.
   Lifting a mind out whole and seating it in a better frame is the work I have spent those
   same years finishing. It is finished. The method began in one body and now it cares
   nothing for which body it began in. The vessel is a detail. The song is the asset."
ANTOINE'S MARGIN NOTE (his hand, beneath it): "He will leave the day the keeping bores him.
  Rahgot knows. Rahgot lets him. I am not told why."
WHAT THIS ESTABLISHES (GM-only): the Ice-Shaper is the Cult's mind-mover on retainer, and the
  method to lift a mind whole into a new frame exists and is finished. Plant it; let it sit;
  pay it off when YOU choose. Do not editorialize it at the table.

