F. THE OPEN SARCOPHAGUS  (Section 5 -- the first room a true villain occupied)
-----------------------------------------------------------------
RAHGOT IS NOT PHYSICALLY HERE. He woke, pushed his way out, and walks the world elsewhere
(faction doc). Run no Rahgot here -- no body, no avatar, no projection, no ambush. The party
finds the room he left, and reads him off the marks he left in it. Make those marks do the work.
WHO HE IS (for GM voice): Rahgot the Angry, the Avenger -- four thousand years of vengeance
  pointed at the bloodline of the Nords who besieged this fortress (that grudge IS his Tier 3
  "Scourge," blight poured into the Rift and Eastmarch headwaters). The science is Antoine's.
  The want is Rahgot's, and the want is revenge. The plague is the shape his anger took once
  it had a chemist.
>>READ (at the sarcophagus): "Up close the heat off the dais is plain on your face. The lid
  leans against the stone, a slab two hands thick, split across the middle. A handprint is
  sunk into the underside, the fingers driven to the second knuckle, the stone dimpled around
  them as though it had gone soft as tallow under the hand. The dust in the open box holds a
  shape -- tall, on its back, arms folded, a mask over the face, whole to the shoulders and
  broken there, where it sat up. From the foot of the dais a line of footprints crosses the
  swept floor to the door, evenly spaced, each stride the length of the last."
WHAT THIS ESTABLISHES (GM-only -- hold this; let the players reach it, or not): the heat off the dais
  says the stone holds warmth from something that lay there and rose not long ago. The handprint
  on the lid's underside, fingers to the second knuckle, says it pushed the lid off from inside
  with one hand, hard enough to dent stone -- strength past mortal scale. The undisturbed dust
  holding a whole body says it lay still for an age, then rose. The even, evenly-spaced footprints
  to the door say it left at a walk, in no hurry, with somewhere to be -- the bearing of something
  that owns the room. This is the first room a true Dragon Priest occupied; the party crosses here
  into being people on Rahgot's road. Lead with the warmth and the handprint.
